    "description": {
      "chat": "",
      "gmnotes": "",
      "short": "",
      "unidentified": "",
      "value": "<p>Ysoki can have long, sharp teeth. A ysoki with this trait is always considered to be armed. They can deal 1d3 lethal piercing damage with unarmed strikes, and the attack doesn’t count as archaic. Ysoki with this trait gain a unique weapon specialization with their natural weapons at 3rd level, allowing them to add 1-1/2 × their character level to their damage rolls for their natural weapons (instead of just adding their character level, as usual).</p>\n<p><strong>This replaces cheek pouches</strong>.</p>\n<p><em>Damage calculation is already set to account the additional damage of 1/2 <span>× their character level, beyond the damage provided by their normal Weapon Specialization damage.</span></em></p>"
